{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/vrc_arenas/pullrequests/2/comments/89088.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/vrc_arenas/pull-requests/2/_/diff#comment-89088"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 2, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/vrc_arenas/pullrequests/2.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/vrc_arenas/pull-requests/2"}}, "title": "install prefix"}, "content": {"raw": "It would be better to not set `CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX` at all.  It's supposed to be set by the user.  Most developers will set it to a sandbox location in their home directories and the debbuilder will explicitly set it to `/usr`.  When it's not set, it'll follow default platform-specific CMake behavior, which is to install into `/usr/local`.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>It would be better to not set <code>CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX</code> at all.  It's supposed to be set by the user.  Most developers will set it to a sandbox location in their home directories and the debbuilder will explicitly set it to <code>/usr</code>.  When it's not set, it'll follow default platform-specific CMake behavior, which is to install into <code>/usr/local</code>.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2013-01-18T19:12:05.357025+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Brian Gerkey", "uuid": "{3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B3d8b5763-9dad-4be7-85c2-a7ab6cd49173%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9/5fa9ec73-0fec-4860-a202-e34ae23b6a12/128"}}, "nickname": "Brian Gerkey", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:2e35028e-9ad8-4d6a-a3a5-275159a304a9"}, "updated_on": "2013-01-18T19:12:05.361011+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 89088}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/vrc_arenas/pullrequests/2/comments/90452.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/vrc_arenas/pull-requests/2/_/diff#comment-90452"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 2, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/vrc_arenas/pullrequests/2.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/vrc_arenas/pull-requests/2"}}, "title": "install prefix"}, "content": {"raw": "Agree with Brian. Is not a good idea to hardcode unconditionally the install path inside the building system. It will break all kind of building tools.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Agree with Brian. Is not a good idea to hardcode unconditionally the install path inside the building system. It will break all kind of building tools.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2013-01-21T16:07:27.610047+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Jose Luis Rivero", "uuid": "{d12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bd12309b2-f745-42ee-b119-aec4fcdf81fe%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/109284c8b83411dbc7492138f6167e9ed=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsJR-5.png"}}, "nickname": "Jose Luis Rivero", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:155a32e2-420c-4d50-98e0-0e722f63f906"}, "updated_on": "2013-01-21T16:07:27.612089+00:00", "type": "pullrequest_comment", "id": 90452}], "page": 1, "size": 2}